Amazon Clone Project

Description
This project is a clone of the popular e-commerce platform, Amazon, built using HTML and CSS. It aims to replicate the key features and design elements of the original Amazon website to showcase proficiency in front-end web development and UI/UX design principles.

Features
Responsive Design: Ensures compatibility across various devices and screen sizes for optimal user experience.
Navigation Bar: Includes dropdown menus and search functionality, mimicking the navigation structure of the official Amazon website.
Product Sections: Different product sections with images and descriptions, allowing users to explore various product categories.
Interactive Elements: Incorporates hover effects and clickable links to enhance user engagement and navigation.
Footer: Comprehensive footer section with links to important pages, providing users with essential information and assistance.
Technologies Used
HTML5: Structured the content and layout of the web pages.
CSS3: Styled the elements and applied custom designs to achieve the desired visual appearance.
Font Awesome: Integrated Font Awesome icons for enhanced visual elements and iconography.
Installation

Explore different product categories by clicking on the navigation links.
Use the search bar to search for specific products.
Hover over product images to see additional details.
Click on the footer links to access important pages such as About Us, Contact, and FAQs.
